    <titleInfo>
        <title>The William Derris Film Collection</title>
    </titleInfo>
    <abstract>The William Derris Collection is comprised of 334 Kodachrome slides and 14 film clips that document seasonal landscapes, flora, wildlife, and the mountain people in the Great Smoky Mountains from the mid-twentieth century. The film clips are paired with newly recorded music appropriate to the Appalachian region.</abstract>
